description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic Community Physiotherapist to work in the Norwich locality team based at Norwich Community Hospital.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will work full time in a supportive Therapy Team visiting patients in their own homes, housing with care and residential settings. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You work independently using lap tops and due to the pandemic, and the team use Microsoft teams for supervision and staff team meetings. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be trained in triage also, and maybe required to cover this part of the service on occasion.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some of the conditions seen in the community are: falls, neurological conditions, stroke, back pain, palliative care and arthritis.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply now to join an organisation that has been awarded an ‘Outstanding’ rating by the Care Quality Commission (CQC), the highest possible rating and the first stand-alone NHS community trust in the country to be awarded the title.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details, please contact Pippa Murrell on 07785233737 or phillippa.murrell@nchc.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
